The paper deals with coding and communication of information, which suggests that it belongs to the Information Theory (cs.IT) category. The use of a dyadic decomposition scheme and the encoding of position and size into the codeword suggest that it may also belong to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Data Structures (cs.DS) categories. The mention of quasiconcave pdfs suggests that it may belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category, which deals with optimization and control theory. Finally, the application of the coding scheme to quantum entanglement suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category, which deals with signal processing and communication.
